Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven
to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{6%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Trim and
halve @Zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into 1⁄2-inch-thick half-moons. Finely
chop @Sun-Dried Tomatoes{1.5%ounce}. Halve, peel, and finely dice @Onion{1}. Peel and
mince @Garlic{1%clove}.

Toss carrots and zucchini on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of
@Olive Oil{}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{} (for 4 servings, spread out across entire sheet).
Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} with 1 TBSP water
(2 TBSP for 4 servings); mix with your hands until pasty. Add @Ground Beef{10%ounce},
@Italian Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, half the sun-dried tomatoes, 2 TBSP onion
(4 TBSP for 4), 1⁄2 tsp salt (1 tsp for 4), and pepper; mix to combine.

Form beef mixture into two 1-inch-tall loaves (four loaves for 4).

Once veggies have roasted 5 minutes, remove sheet from oven. Carefully add meatloaves
to empty side of sheet. (For 4 servings, leave veggies roasting; add meatloaves to a
second baking sheet and bake on middle rack.) Return to top rack; roast until
meatloaves are cooked through and veggies are browned and tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

== Couscous ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat.
Add @Israeli Couscous{2.5%ounce} and half the remaining onion; cook, stirring, until
couscous is lightly toasted and onion is softened, ~{4-6%minutes}. Add garlic and
cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in 3⁄4 cup water (1 1⁄4 cups for 4 servings); bring to a boil, then cover and
reduce to a low simmer. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Garlic-Onion Sauce ==

While couscous cooks, heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in a #small pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add remaining onion and remaining sun-dried tomatoes; cook,
stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with a pinch of salt and
pepper.

Add half the @Chicken Stock Concentrate{2}, 1/3 cup water, and @Sugar{1/4%tsp}
(3⁄4 cup water and 1⁄2 tsp sugar for 4 servings); cook, stirring occasionally, until
thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

> For a thinner sauce, stir in water a splash at a time until you reach your desired
> consistency.

Turn off heat. Stir in @Cream Cheese{2%tablespoon} until smooth and fully
incorporated. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

== To Serve ==

To #pot{} with couscous, stir in @Butter{1 1/2%TBSP} (3 TBSP for 4 servings) and
remaining stock concentrate. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide meatloaves, couscous, and roasted veggies between plates. Drizzle meatloaves
with as much sauce as you like. Serve with any remaining sauce on the side.

> Ground Meat is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.